description:
The Superior Spider-Man battles Cardiac! Plus: is it all over for Doc Ock as the Avengers confront the Wall-Crawler?!

By: Dan Slott and Humberto Ramos.

Plus, the Superior Spider-Man hatches a mysterious plan to rescue the Chameleon from S.H.I.E.L.D. custody! However, the Master of Mimicry’s former Russian paymasters want him dead!

By: Christopher Yost and Marco Checchetto.

Also, the Scarlet Spider faces the fury of the Rangers, and Roxxon's sinister secret is revealed!

By: Christopher Yost and Khoi Pham.

Includes material reprinted from Superior Spider-Man #7, Avenging Spider-Man #20 and Scarlet Spider Vol.2 #8!

An 'Avengers vs X-Men' chapter!

Five X-Men now wield the awesome power of the Phoenix! They intend to remake the world – and they're going to start by destroying Mr Sinister!

By Kieron Gillen, Daniel Acuna and Michael Del Mundo.

Includes material first featured in Uncanny X-Men #15-17.
The Fabulous Five battle a creature so dangerous that he will change the team forever. Be here for the final issue of The Fabulous Five.
name: Behold G.L.O.M.

description:
An 'Avengers vs X-Men' chapter!

Hercules battles Sebastian Shaw – and the young mutants of Utopia clash with the Avengers Academy students!

By Christos Gage and Tom Grummett.

'Villains For Hire'! A supervillain war erupts in New York as the Purple Man's forces are attacked by a mysterious rival group!

By Dan Abnett, Andy Lanning and Renato Arlem.

Daredevil has one hope for survival: Giant-Man! Get ready for a fantastic voyage inside the brain of the Man Without Fear!

By Mark Waid and Chris Samnee.

Includes material first featured in Daredevil #16, Villains for Hire #1 and Avengers Academy #30-31.

This comic has been printed and reprinted from the original after which the last publisher Standaard Uitgeverij had two more issues commissioned.

description:
Ellen is a young English lady, thirty-something, living in London and married to a director. She leads a quiet and comfortable life until two young women are found murdered.

An unstoppable mechanism springs into life and starts to crush her harmonious life. She also has no idea she only has six days to live.
name: Tea Time

description:
Ellen's life now lies in ruin. Her husband has been acquitted of the murder of the two young women, but when Ellen finds out the women were her husbands lovers she leaves him and moves in with her friend Beth.

This issue builds on the tension left by the fist issue. If Ellen's husband isn't the killer then who is? When this issue starts Ellen only has two days to live.

description: Back from the pages of Luftwaffe: 1946, now in full color, Col. J.J. Condorcet's special Commando team once again uses their special submarine, the Hunley (named after the Civil War Confederate sub of the same name) to pursue another Nazi carrier, the Potsdam, shortly after concluding their Operation Saturn in 1946. En route, the team runs afoul of a special Type XXI U-boat towing a submerged V-2 rocket aimed at Washington D.C., and must divert to stop that. But then an emergency arises and J.J. must hurry off to meet his most dangerous ally, Comrade Birdboy, aka Yosef Soyuz, to prevent the Soviets from obtaining the Nazi's darkest secret, the Black Holocaust. Accompanying him are the men of the X-Corps, led by Lt. Stoner and Sgt. Morrow. Facing them are their counterparts, Sgt. Blitzer and the Sonderkommando Oberlicht (as in Mika Oberlicht, J.J.'s nemesis), created specially by Hitler to destroy the Hunley Commandos!

It is the year Universal Century 0079, and the eighth month of the vicious One Year War between the Earth Federation and a breakaway nation of space colonists, the Principality of Zeon. The story follows the crew of the ship White Base, as they fight to ferry the experimental RX-78-02 Gundam mobile suit to the Federation base at Jaburo.
